<p>Philadelphia homeowners can access multiple rebate programs to offset HVAC installation costs. Federal tax credits provide up to \$2,000 for qualifying heat pumps and \$600 for high-efficiency air conditioners installed through 2032. Pennsylvania's Act 129 program, administered through PECO, offers rebates of \$300-800 for ENERGY STAR certified air conditioners and heat pumps, plus additional incentives for smart thermostats (\$75-100). PECO's Energy Efficiency Programs provide rebates up to \$1,200 for qualifying heat pump installations and \$400-600 for high-efficiency central air systems. Low-income households may qualify for additional assistance through Pennsylvania's LIHEAP Crisis Program and Weatherization Assistance Program, which can cover significant portions of HVAC replacement costs for eligible residents.</p>

